5:
Floretta, we just got another order
from the orphanage.
10:
Wh-what?! Another one?! I can't
keep up!
14: They said it's for the children.
19:
D-don't say that... How can I say no
to orphans?!
24:
Geez... You only gave baranki out to
a few people. Who would've
guessed they'd get so popular.
29:
The people here are always on the
lookout for new trends. I'm sure
there'll be copycat shops popping
up in no time.
33:
I sure hope so! It's not like I invented
them anyway.
37:
You're not making any money off of
these, correct? If it's too much work,
why not just say no?
42:
I-it's not that I mind doing it! I'm
actually thrilled to know people like
something I made...
46:
Ah, but I don't have enough time to
complete this order! What am I
gonna dooo?!
52:
Arriving in the knick of time! Captain
Marina, at your service!
63:
Mm-mm! Your baranki are so good!
I've tried to make them myself, but I
can never get them right.
67:
Ahaha... Sorry I roped you into
helping me. Especially when you're
visiting after so long...
73:
No worries! I can't NOT help my
adorable little Floretta.
78:
You really did show up at the perfect
time though. Was it just dumb luck?
83:
No way. Floretta contacted us sayin'
she wanted to meet the cap'n. We
were originally goin' to meet up, but...
86:
She didn't show up. Knowing her, I
thought she might be in trouble, so I
figured checking on her wouldn't
hurt.
90:
You're as amazing as ever, Captain.
You always see right through me.
94:
You wanted to give some baranki to
the cap'n, right? Then this is the
perfect time.
99:
They aren't just for her. I want you
guys to have some too. Although,
admittedly, they're a bit simple for
Fioletovy Den presents.
110: Captain? What are you doing up?
114:
Hm, I'm feeling a bit lonely all by
myself. The boys are down for the
count, so come join me!
119:
I-I'm not drinking, okay? And you
haven't been trying to get Alk and
the others drunk, have you?
123:
Of course not. I've got better things
in store for them.
127:
You seem to be getting along with
them though. Looks like someone's
coming out of her shell.
131: A-am I? I can't really tell.
135:
Um, Captain, I didn't get to say it
earlier, but...
137:
I'm... sorry I sunk your ship back then.
I didn't mean—
142:
Floretta, if you're gonna apologize,
that's not what I want you to
apologize for.
146:
Do you know how worried I was
when you just... disappeared?
152:
...You're right. I'm sorry for leaving
like that.
158:
Hey, tell me a bit more about your
hometown. I hear you've got a friend
back there too.
162:
Ahaha... Lemme guess, Stella told
you?
165:
Maybe. She mentioned you want to
see them again. What's your buddy
like?
170:
Alaimi... was always so kind, so
warm, and so cheerful... I guess you
could say I wanted to be like her.
174:
Gotcha. Is she where you get that
spunk of yours?
177:
I suppose so... When I left our island, I
might have tried to be more like
Alaimi.
179:
I was actually a really quiet person
as a kid. I might have gone a bit
overboard pretending to be
something I'm not.
182: I see. So then why did you—
186:
Ah, you know what? Forget it. I don't
wanna pry too much. I'm just glad I
got my Fioletovy Den present.
Thanks again.
195:
Ahaha, um, you see... Uhh, how do I
put this...
200:
Don't worry, I'm not going anywhere.
Take your time and figure out what
you want to say. Hehe, some things
never change, do they?
204:
You see... There's something I should
have apologized to Alaimi for.
205:
But instead, I ran away. And then... I
did the same thing to you.
210:
I screwed up, and because of that...
Alaimi had to give up on her dream.
Things got weird between us, so I—
215:
You idiot. How can you know it's your
fault if you've never even asked?
219: You're friends, right? Just go visit her.
222:
As a former member of the Crimson
Blades, you need to steady your
resolve and fight!
230:
I already told myself I won't run, so... I
guess I have no choice but to move
forward.
235:
Aw, come on, no need to look so
serious. Your smile is your greatest
weapon, you know.
239:
Also, think you could make some
more baranki? Enough to impress
this friend of yours.
243:
Ahaha, that might be a good idea...
Then I'll have a chance to teach you
how to make them as well.
